The Apps Manager UI supports several Spring Boot Actuator endpoints. This topic describes how to configure your app so that Apps Manager displays data from the Actuator endpoints. 

For information on how you use these endpoints in Apps Manager, see the [Using Spring Boot Actuator Endpoints in Apps Manager](./using-actuators.html). 

## <a id='actuator'></a> Overview: Actuator Endpoints

Spring Boot Actuator provides services for monitoring and managing your Spring Boot app. You can add these services to your app project and access them through HTTP endpoints.   

